 for bestpractices and # Dashboard

## Overview
You are building the Dashboard module for Gbox360, a secure, enterprise-grade investor narrative intelligence platform. The Dashboard is the primary authenticated landing experience where users pick a company and a time window, inspect their saved companies, and view current IPI quick-summary cards. This page serves as the entry point to deeper drill-downs, comparisons, and narrative explanations. All UI must be visually polished, accessible, and designed with robust runtime safety as described in the mandatory coding standards.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Dashboard page is the authenticated landing surface that aggregates the core IPI workflow. It presents a searchable, auto-complete company picker, time window presets (including a custom range), a grid of IPI quick-summary cards for the selected company, a pane listing saved/recent companies with quick score indicators, and system status banners. It also includes a global header with company search, user avatar/menu, and quick-help/settings actions. The page acts as the launchpad to Company View (IPI Detail) and cross-company comparisons, and it must gracefully handle cases where data is loading or missing.

Goals:
- Provide a fast, scannable overview of IPI per company and time window with transparent numerics and clear directional signals.
- Enable quick drill-down to Why did this move? and deeper narratives.
- Present saved/suggested companies with actionable scores to facilitate comparison.
- Surface ingestion status, staleness warnings, and notifications to keep users informed.
- Maintain a consistent, enterprise-grade visual language aligned with the design system and the strict runtime safety rules provided.

Connected features:
- Simplified IPI Calculation: For the selected company and time window, compute IPI using Narrative (40%), Credibility (40%), and Risk proxy (20%). Provide directional change (↑/↓) and the top 3 narrative contributions.
- Company Selection & Time Window Controls: A searchable company picker with auto-complete, plus a list of recent/saved companies and time-window presets with a custom date-range option.
- Visual emphasis on the IPI score, directional arrow, sparkline visualizing narrative persistence, and chips for top narratives.
- Saved Companies Pane: List of user-saved companies with quick score badges, allowing rapid swaps.
- Notifications / System Status: Banner(s) for ingestion status, staleness, and other system health indicators.
- Footer: About/Help/Privacy links and secondary navigation items.
- Data flow integration points:
  - Frontend consumes data from (or mocks for) endpoints that supply company lists, saved companies, IPI values, top narratives, and time window data.
  - No external API integration is strictly required for MVP; the design accommodates future API connections while preserving strict runtime safety.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Global Header: Left-aligned brand, central or left-aligned navigation, right-aligned user avatars and action items (Help, Settings, Logout).
- Company Selector: Auto-complete input with suggestion dropdown, recent/saved companies section, and a compact grid/list of results.
- Time Window Selector: Presets (1D, 1W, 1M, 3M, YTD) plus a custom date-range picker with clear start/end date fields.
- IPI Quick Card Grid: For the selected company, a compact card showing IPI score (large numerals), directional arrow, a sparkline showing narrative persistence, a row of top narrative chips (colored by #FF6B4A for emphasis), and a bottom-right CTA to view details.
- Saved Companies Pane: Compact list with company name, short ticker or alias, and a small score badge; ability to pin/unpin or select for quick switching.
- System Status Banner: Inline alert with status icon/text and optional action to refresh or view details.
- Footer: Standard enterprise staff links and legal notices.

Visual style notes:
- Use the provided color palette and typography guidelines to ensure consistency with the rest of the product.
- Cards have subtle borders (#E5E7EB) and soft shadows; hover states emphasize elevation without overpowering the page.
- Primary CTAs use the accent #0F172A; secondary states use a lighter border approach with #E5E7EB.

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety (CRITICAL)
- Supabase query results: Always use nullish coalescing — const items = data ?? []. Supabase returns null when there are no rows.
- Array methods: Never call on a value that could be null/undefined. Guard with (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
- React useState for arrays/objects: Initialize with correct type, e.g., useState<T[]>([]).
- API response shapes: Validate responses, e.g., const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Optional chaining: Use optional chaining for nested API results.
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.

PROJECT CONTEXT SUMMARY (Key Constraints)
- Target Page: Dashboard
- No hard requirement for real API connections in MVP, but the structure must be ready for API integration.
- Data model hints: IPI scores, directional change, top narratives (with potential IDs, weights, and timestamps), and a list of saved/recent companies.
- End-to-end flow should be intuitive: select company + time window → see IPI score and top drivers → drill down for Why did this move? → optionally compare with other companies.

## Components to Build
- DashboardLayout
  - Props: user, currentCompanyId, currentWindow, savedCompanies, systemStatus
  - Responsibilities: global header, responsive layout scaffolding, route/section anchors, universal loading/error states.
- CompanySearchBar
  - Features: auto-complete, suggestions as user types, keyboard navigation, accessibility attributes.
  - Data: fetch or mock company list; expose onSelect callback.
  - Safeties: guard against null/undefined results; ensure suggestions render only when an array.
- TimeWindowPicker
  - Features: presets and a custom date-range selection (startDate, endDate). Validate that endDate >= startDate; handle invalid ranges gracefully.
- IPIQuickCard
  - Props: company, window, ipiScore, direction, topNarratives, sparklineData
  - Visuals: large numeric IPI, directional indicator, sparkline, chips for top narratives, and a CTA “View details”.
- SavedCompaniesPane
  - Props: savedCompanies[]; onSelectCompany; onUnpin
  - Safeties: map over (savedCompanies ?? []) with Array.isArray guard.
- SystemStatusBanner
  - Props: status, message, canRetry
- CompanyViewLink (drill-down trigger)
  - Simple CTA to navigate to Why did this move? view.
- IPIBarChart or Sparkline
  - Lightweight visualization to reflect narrative persistence. Minimal dependencies to avoid heavy charts; pure SVG path generation is acceptable.
- NotificationsPanel
  - Optional banners for ingestion status and staleness.
- Footer
  - Static links consistent with design.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Tech stack compatibility: React (with hooks), TypeScript preferred for type safety.
- State management: component state with useState/useEffect; lift global state to DashboardContext if needed for cross-page consistency.
- Accessibility: aria-labels, roles, keyboard navigation for all interactive elements; high-contrast text where required.
- Null safety and guards: Apply runtime safety rules in all data handling:
  - Use (data ?? []) for arrays from fetch/post results.
  - Use Array.isArray for array checks before mapping/filtering.
  - Always initialize useState with [] for array data; initialize with appropriate defaults for objects.
- Data handling:
  - Mock data when APIs are not connected, but keep interfaces ready for real API endpoints.
  - Validate input ranges for custom date pickers; show validation messages if invalid.
- UI interactions:
  - Debounced search in CompanySearchBar to minimize API calls or heavy filtering.
  - Dynamic loading skeletons for IPI cards while data loads.
  - Smooth transitions for card hover, list updates, and drill-down panels (180ms to 300ms).
- Data formatting:
  - IPI score as numeric with 2 decimal places.
  - Direction indicator as "↑" or "↓" with a color cue (green for up, red/orange for down, using appropriate CSS tokens).
  - Sparkline data as an inline SVG path; guard against insufficient data.
- Data persistence:
  - Saved companies stored in local state; in a production scenario, backed by user profile in the backend. Ensure no direct mutation of saved arrays.

### Backend
- As per project context, no mandatory external API connections are required for MVP. However, define interfaces for:
  - Endpoints (if later connected):
    - GET /companies?query=... -> Company[] with id, name, ticker
    - GET /users/{userId}/saved-companies -> Company[] with score
    - GET /ipi?companyId&startDate=&endDate= -> { ipiScore, direction, topNarratives: { id, label, weight }[], sparkline: number[] }
    - GET /system-status -> { status, message, lastUpdated }
- Database schemas (for future integration):
  - users: id, email, name, preferences
  - saved_companies: user_id, company_id, score, last_seen
  - ipi_results: company_id, start_date, end_date, score, direction
  - narratives: id, company_id, timestamp, source, text, weight, credibility

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - Dashboard fetches saved companies and company list on mount.
  - When a company or date window changes, fetch IPI summary for the current selection.
  - On selecting a saved company, immediately update the UI with the corresponding IPI data.
  - The Company View (IPI Detail) link uses the current selection to navigate to the detail view with preloaded data or fetches on demand.
- Error handling:
  - Graceful UI fallbacks if data is missing; show a helpful empty state with copy and a retry button.
  - Centralized error boundaries for fetch failures.
- State synchronization:
  - Ensure that when the user changes the time window, the IPI card content updates consistently and does not cause stale data illusions.
- Performance:
  - Lazy load or render skeletons for IPI cards while data is being fetched.
  - Use memoization (React.memo) for components with large props like IPIQuickCard to minimize unnecessary re-renders.

## User Experience Flow
1) User lands on Dashboard (authenticated):
   - Global header presents a company search with auto-complete.
   - Time Window presets are visible with a custom range option.
   - A grid of IPI Quick Cards is shown for the currently selected company (default to the most recently saved or a recommended company).
   - Saved Companies Pane displays top saved targets with quick scores.
   - System Status Banner shows ingestion status or staleness, if applicable.
2) User interacts with CompanySearchBar:
   - Typing filters suggestions; pressing Enter or selecting a suggestion selects the company and updates the IPI card grid.
3) User uses TimeWindowPicker:
   - Selecting a preset updates the IPI summary; a custom date range validates for correctness and updates if valid.
4) User analyzes IPI Quick Cards:
   - Each card displays IPI score, direction, a sparkline, and top narrative chips. A “View details” CTA navigates to the Company View (IPI Detail) for deeper drill-down.
5) User opens Saved Companies Pane:
   - Click a saved company to switch the dashboard view; optionally unpin or update the score badge.
6) User needs more context:
   - Click the Why did this move? CTA on the Company View to reveal narrative events behind the movement.
7) Non-authenticated exploration:
   - If allowed by the product, provide a limited demo flow with a mock or guest session, ensuring sensitive data remains protected.

## Technical Specifications

Data Models:
- Company
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - ticker: string
  - logoUrl?: string
- IPIResult
  - companyId: string
  - startDate: string (ISO)
  - endDate: string (ISO)
  - score: number
  - direction: 'up' | 'down' | 'flat'
  - topNarratives: NarrativeContribution[]
  - sparkline: number[]
- NarrativeContribution
  - id: string
  - label: string
  - weight: number
  - source: string
  - credibility: number
  - timestamp?: string
- SavedCompany
  - companyId: string
  - userId: string
  - score: number
  - lastViewed?: string
  - pinned?: boolean

API Endpoints (for MVP-ready API integration):
- GET /api/companies?query=&limit=
  - Returns: { data: Company[] | null }
- GET /api/users/{userId}/saved-companies
  - Returns: { data: SavedCompany[] | null }
- GET /api/ipi?companyId=&startDate=&endDate=
  - Returns: { data: IPIResult | null }
- GET /api/system-status
  - Returns: { data: { status: string, message: string, lastUpdated: string } | null }

Security:
- Authentication via session-based or token-based mechanism.
- Authorization checks to ensure only authenticated users fetch personal saved companies and IPI data tied to their account.
- All API calls must handle 401/403 gracefully and prompt re-auth if needed.

Validation:
- Date range: startDate must be <= endDate; endDate cannot be in the future beyond allowed horizon.
- Company selection: Ensure selected companyId exists within the known company list; if not, treat as invalid and reset to a safe default.
- IPI values: Validate numeric ranges for score (e.g., 0-100 or as defined by domain), direction, and narratives.

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Dashboard renders with a header, time window controls, company search, saved companies pane, and a responsive IPI Quick Card Grid.
- [ ] Selecting a company or time window updates IPI score, direction, and top narratives; data is safely guarded for null values (e.g., (data ?? []) usage).
- [ ] All array operations are performed on guaranteed arrays or guarded via Array.isArray checks or (items ?? []) strategies.
- [ ] useState initializations for all array data use correct default types, e.g., useState<IPIResult[]>([]) or useState<Company[]>([]).
- [ ] No runtime crashes due to null/undefined values when rendering lists or mapping over results.
- [ ] The UI adheres to the provided color palette, typography scale, and spacing guidelines.
- [ ] Drill-down path to Company View (IPI Detail) is functional with a clear CTA and correct data passage.
- [ ] Accessibility checks pass for interactive elements (ARIA labels, focus states, keyboard navigation).
- [ ] Data loading states (skeletons) and error states are visible and actionable.

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Maintain the modern, trust-focused aesthetic with restrained color accents.
- Emphasize clarity and scannability: big IPI scores, concise top narratives, and intuitive controls.
- Use transitions and micro-interactions that feel enterprise-grade (180–320ms durations).
- Ensure consistent left-aligned text blocks, predictable margins, and a calm vertical rhythm (48–64px between major sections).

Visual Style

Color Palette
- Primary background: #FBFBFC
- Map/background overlay: #F3F4F6
- Primary text: #111827
- Secondary text / meta: #6B7280
- Borders / dividers: #E5E7EB
- Card background / surfaces: #FFFFFF
- Accent callouts / badges: #FF6B4A
- Accent primary CTA: #0F172A
- Accent focus / highlights: #93C5FD
- Muted success/credibility: #10B981

Typography & Layout
- Font family: Inter / SF Pro / system-ui
- Hierarchy: H1 48–56px; H2 24–32px; Body 16px; Micro 12–14px; Numeric stats 28–36px
- Grid: 12-column responsive; generous vertical rhythm; card paddings 20–28px; controls 12–16px
- Visual treatments: bold numerals for metrics; chips for narratives; restrained caps for small UI text

Key Design Elements
- Card design: white surfaces, subtle borders, soft shadows, 10–12px radii, hover lift
- Navigation: top bar with brand, active states, pill action buttons
- Data Visualization: simple sparklines, minimal lines, light grids
- Interactive Elements: rounded inputs, blue focus outlines, accessible hover/focus
- Micro-interactions: 150–220ms hover transitions; 300ms panel transitions
- Accessibility: high contrast text, keyboard focus, aria-labels

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety (repeatable)
- Always guard against null/undefined values in arrays and API results.
- Use data ?? [] for results; Array.isArray checks; correct useState defaults for arrays.
- Validate and safely destructure API responses with defaults.

Connected Pages and Features (for context)
- Company View (IPI Detail)
- Login Page
- Settings & Preferences
- All designed to integrate with the Dashboard’s IPI data flow and UI scaffolding.

Deliverables
- A fully-typed React (TypeScript) implementation blueprint with:
  - Component interfaces and props
  - Data-fetch abstractions with safe guards
  - State management patterns
  - CSS-in-JS or CSS modules consistent with the design system
  - Accessibility notes and ARIA considerations
- Clear file structure indicating components, hooks, and helpers
- Sample mocked data aligned with the models above for MVP demonstration
- Documentation on how to wire in real API endpoints when available

If you need, I can provide a scaffolded file tree and starter code snippets (TypeScript React components, hooks for data access, and minimal styling) that adhere to all runtime safety rules outlined above. for style.

CRITICAL DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:
- You MUST follow ALL design principles and patterns specified in the Design Reference above
- Do NOT deviate from the design specifications without explicit user permission
- Implement ALL visual design elements (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, animations) as specified
- Follow the layout patterns and component designs exactly as documented
- Ensure all interactions and micro-animations match the reference specifications

CRITICAL TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:
- React 18.3.1, React Router 6.30.1
- Tailwind CSS v3 with tailwind.config.js and custom keyframes
- @tailwindcss/typography plugin for rich text content
- Tailwind CSS animations (NOT Motion library or framer-motion)
- Sonner for toasts
- Recharts for data visualization
- Native fetch() with API utilities in src/lib/api.ts
- Design system with CSS custom properties
- Use RGB color values for theming
- When Supabase is configured: use Edge Functions for LLM and server-only logic; never expose API keys in the client

