  - Returns: { data: IPIResult | null }
- GET /api/system-status
  - Returns: { data: { status: string, message: string, lastUpdated: string } | null }

Security:
- Authentication via session-based or token-based mechanism.
- Authorization checks to ensure only authenticated users fetch personal saved companies and IPI data tied to their account.
- All API calls must handle 401/403 gracefully and prompt re-auth if needed.

Validation:
- Date range: startDate must be <= endDate; endDate cannot be in the future beyond allowed horizon.
- Company selection: Ensure selected companyId exists within the known company list; if not, treat as invalid and reset to a safe default.
- IPI values: Validate numeric ranges for score (e.g., 0-100 or as defined by domain), direction, and narratives.

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Dashboard renders with a header, time window controls, company search, saved companies pane, and a responsive IPI Quick Card Grid.
- [ ] Selecting a company or time window updates IPI score, direction, and top narratives; data is safely guarded for null values (e.g., (data ?? []) usage).
- [ ] All array operations are performed on guaranteed arrays or guarded via Array.isArray checks or (items ?? []) strategies.
- [ ] useState initializations for all array data use correct default types, e.g., useState<IPIResult[]>([]) or useState<Company[]>([]).
- [ ] No runtime crashes due to null/undefined values when rendering lists or mapping over results.
- [ ] The UI adheres to the provided color palette, typography scale, and spacing guidelines.
- [ ] Drill-down path to Company View (IPI Detail) is functional with a clear CTA and correct data passage.
- [ ] Accessibility checks pass for interactive elements (ARIA labels, focus states, keyboard navigation).
- [ ] Data loading states (skeletons) and error states are visible and actionable.

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Maintain the modern, trust-focused aesthetic with restrained color accents.
- Emphasize clarity and scannability: big IPI scores, concise top narratives, and intuitive controls.
- Use transitions and micro-interactions that feel enterprise-grade (180–320ms durations).
- Ensure consistent left-aligned text blocks, predictable margins, and a calm vertical rhythm (48–64px between major sections).

Visual Style

Color Palette
- Primary background: #FBFBFC
- Map/background overlay: #F3F4F6
- Primary text: #111827
- Secondary text / meta: #6B7280
- Borders / dividers: #E5E7EB
- Card background / surfaces: #FFFFFF
- Accent callouts / badges: #FF6B4A
- Accent primary CTA: #0F172A
- Accent focus / highlights: #93C5FD
- Muted success/credibility: #10B981

Typography & Layout
- Font family: Inter / SF Pro / system-ui
- Hierarchy: H1 48–56px; H2 24–32px; Body 16px; Micro 12–14px; Numeric stats 28–36px
- Grid: 12-column responsive; generous vertical rhythm; card paddings 20–28px; controls 12–16px
- Visual treatments: bold numerals for metrics; chips for narratives; restrained caps for small UI text

Key Design Elements
- Card design: white surfaces, subtle borders, soft shadows, 10–12px radii, hover lift
- Navigation: top bar with brand, active states, pill action buttons
- Data Visualization: simple sparklines, minimal lines, light grids
- Interactive Elements: rounded inputs, blue focus outlines, accessible hover/focus
- Micro-interactions: 150–220ms hover transitions; 300ms panel transitions
- Accessibility: high contrast text, keyboard focus, aria-labels

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety (repeatable)
- Always guard against null/undefined values in arrays and API results.
- Use data ?? [] for results; Array.isArray checks; correct useState defaults for arrays.
- Validate and safely destructure API responses with defaults.

Connected Pages and Features (for context)
- Company View (IPI Detail)
- Login Page
- Settings & Preferences
- All designed to integrate with the Dashboard’s IPI data flow and UI scaffolding.

Deliverables
- A fully-typed React (TypeScript) implementation blueprint with:
  - Component interfaces and props
  - Data-fetch abstractions with safe guards
  - State management patterns
  - CSS-in-JS or CSS modules consistent with the design system
  - Accessibility notes and ARIA considerations
- Clear file structure indicating components, hooks, and helpers
- Sample mocked data aligned with the models above for MVP demonstration
- Documentation on how to wire in real API endpoints when available

